#################### getting Drosophila genome degeneracy scores ####################

First I used https://github.com/harvardinformatics/degenotate to find 0 fold and 4 fold positions within the fly genome using NCBI annotation (gff) and genome (GCF_000001215.4_Release_6_plus_ISO1_MT_genomic.fna) using degenotate.sh:


python degenotate.py \
  -a genomic.gff \
  -g GCF_000001215.4_Release_6_plus_ISO1_MT_genomic.fna \
  -o degenotate_ncbi_out \
  --overwrite \
  -d " "



This produces degeneracy-all-sites.bed: a bed-like file that contains the degeneracy score (0-, 2-, 3-, or 4-fold) of every coding site

#################### getting 0 and 4 fold sites ####################

Then I got 0 and 4 fold sites using 4_0_fold.py:

import gzip

DEGEN_BED = "degenotate_ncbi_out/degeneracy-all-sites.bed"
OUT_4D = "fourfold_sites.bed"
OUT_0D = "zerofold_sites.bed"

with open(DEGEN_BED, "rt") as f, open(OUT_4D, "w") as o4, open(OUT_0D, "w") as o0:
    for line in f:
        if not line.strip() or line.startswith("#"):
            continue
        chrom, start, end, site_id, deg, *rest = line.rstrip("\n").split("\t")
        if deg == "4":
            o4.write(f"{chrom}\t{start}\t{end}\n")
        elif deg == "0":
            o0.write(f"{chrom}\t{start}\t{end}\n")

print("Wrote", OUT_4D, "and", OUT_0D)



#################### ranaming scaffold ids to chromosome name ####################

This is done using the rename.py file, which produces:

zerofold_sites.destnames.bed
fourfold_sites.destnames.bed



